&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;SURGERY AND GASTROENTEROLOGY CARE GROUP&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;GASTROENTEROLOGY DEPARTMENT&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;MEDICAL SECRETARY (BAND 3) &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;A vacancy has arisen within the within the Gastroenterology Department for an experienced Band 3 Medical Secretary. This is a 37.5 hours per week post and hours will be worked over five days.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Reporting to the team leader, the post holder will be involved with a wide range of duties including clinic typing, telephone enquiries, admin and non-admitted PTL. The post holder must have the ability to organise and prioritise their workload effectively, and work on their own initiative. Applicants must have excellent communication skills, an organised and methodical approach to their duties and enjoy a very driven secretarial role.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Lorraine Hankey&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Team Leader&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Lorraine.hankey@dchft.nhs.uk&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;01305 255393&lt;/p&gt;
